1
00:00:02,180 --> 00:00:03,810
Previously on Friends:

2
00:00:03,970 --> 00:00:05,540
Erica, are you okay?

3
00:00:05,540 --> 00:00:06,740
Yeah, you know, maybe I ate too much.

4
00:00:06,810 --> 00:00:11,520
I keep getting these stomachaches. They come and go, like, every few minutes.

5
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:17,570
-Oh, my God. -Relax, we'll just get her some antacids.

6
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:20,700
She doesn't have a stomachache! She's in labor!

7
00:00:20,870 --> 00:00:21,910
Oh, my God!

8
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:24,030
If you think that I didn't say goodbye...

9
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,620
...because you don't mean as much to me as everybody else, you're wrong.

10
00:00:27,790 --> 00:00:29,580
It's because you mean more to me.

11
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:31,670
-Rach! -What?

12
00:00:55,650 --> 00:00:56,460
Hey.

13
00:00:58,390 --> 00:01:01,360
Go back to sleep. I have to go home.

14
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:04,990
Oh, God. This was amazing.

15
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,550
It really was.

16
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,530
You've learned some new moves.

17
00:01:11,950 --> 00:01:15,380
Yeah, well, this guy at work gave me <i>Sex for Dummies</i>

18
00:01:15,430 --> 00:01:16,620
as a joke.

19
00:01:17,010 --> 00:01:18,920
- Who's laughing now? - I am.

20
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:22,750
《老友记》第十季第十七  十八集  说再见

21
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:13,620
Breathe...

22
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,690
Okay. Good.

23
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:18,760
Next time, can I say "breathe"?

24
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,800
No. Last time, you said it like Dracula,

25
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,570
and it scared her.

26
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:25,550
Can I get you anything? You want some more ice chips?

27
00:02:25,550 --> 00:02:26,670
No, I'm okay.

28
00:02:26,670 --> 00:02:28,420
All right. I'll be right back.

29
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,450
- Where you going? - To use the bathroom.

30
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:36,840
- You can't leave me alone with her. - What?

31
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:40,200
This is exactly the kind of social situation...

32
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,760
...that I am not comfortable with.

33
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:46,810
What kind of social situation are you comfortable with?

34
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:50,940
It's just that we've never spent any time, you know, alone together.

35
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,580
You'll be fine.

36
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:54,830
You won't, but I'll be back in two minutes.

37
00:02:54,830 --> 00:02:56,230
Okay.

38
00:03:03,170 --> 00:03:07,600
So any plans for the summer?

39
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:12,590
I don't know. Maybe church camp.

40
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:19,140
May not want to mention this.

41
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:24,700
So you ever wonder which is worse?

42
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:28,270
You know, going through labor or getting kicked in the nuts?

43
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:33,010
- What? - Oh, it's just interesting.

44
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,160
Because no one will ever know

45
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:38,050
because no one can experience both.

46
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:45,290
One of life's great unanswerable questions.

47
00:03:46,850 --> 00:03:48,610
Who knows? Maybe there's something

48
00:03:48,610 --> 00:03:51,450
even more painful than those things.

49
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:56,110
Like this.

50
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:03,990
- Come in. - Morning.

51
00:04:03,990 --> 00:04:06,100
- Hey. - What's that?

52
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,390
Oh, it's my housewarming present for Monica and Chandler.

53
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,070
That's a baby chick and duck.

54
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:16,170
And I named them Chick Jr. And Duck Jr.

55
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:18,690
I did not see that coming.

56
00:04:19,530 --> 00:04:20,940
They'll love it at that new house.

57
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,540
It has that big backyard.

58
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:23,540
When they're old,

59
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:24,850
they'll go to that farm...

60
00:04:24,850 --> 00:04:27,620
...that Chandler took the other chick and duck to.

61
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,830
- Yes. - Yeah.

62
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,660
It's a shame people can't visit there.

63
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:34,800
That is the rule though.

64
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:41,050
Guess what. You're almost an uncle.

65
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:41,670
What?

66
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,270
Erica went into labor last night.

67
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:45,000
Monica and Chandler are at the hospital right now.

68
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:48,340
- Oh, my God! - I have a feeling it's gonna be a girl.

69
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:50,950
Phoebe, you were sure Ben was gonna be a girl.

70
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:53,000
Have you seen him throw a ball?

71
00:04:56,010 --> 00:04:59,740
- Is Rachel here? - I think she's still asleep.

72
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:01,160
How did it go with you guys last night?

73
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:03,290
She seemed pretty pissed at you.

74
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:06,660
We worked things out.

75
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,180
What's that smile?

76
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,840
Did something happen with you two?

77
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:13,400
Hey, I'm not one to kiss and tell.

78
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,980
But I'm also not one to have sex and shut up.

79
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,820
We totally did it.

80
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,580
Oh, my God. You and Rachel?

81
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:22,420
I know, it's pretty great.

82
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:23,560
So, what does that mean?

83
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,050
Are you guys getting back together?

84
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:26,720
Oh, I don't know.

85
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,390
We didn't really get to talk.

86
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:30,190
But do you want to get back together?

87
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,670
I don't know.

88
00:05:32,450 --> 00:05:33,680
It was incredible.

89
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,260
I mean, it just felt so right.

90
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:38,050
When I was holding her,

91
00:05:38,050 --> 00:05:40,860
I mean, I never wanted to let her go.

92
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:45,170
Know what? Yeah, I do. I want to be together.

93
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,960
So is she still going to Paris?

94
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:53,890
Wow, I hadn't thought of that. I hope not.

95
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:56,650
This is, like, the best day ever. Ever.

96
00:05:56,650 --> 00:05:58,150
You guys might get back together.

97
00:05:58,150 --> 00:05:59,920
Monica and Chandler get their baby.

98
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,160
There are chicks and ducks...

99
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,100
...in the world again.

100
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:06,420
I feel like I'm in a musical.

101
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,090
Morning.

102
00:06:14,090 --> 00:06:16,100
Guess you'll never know how it ends.

103
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,240
- Hey. - Hi.

104
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:22,340
- Hi. How'd you sleep? - Good. You?

105
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:24,930
- Good. - I'll bet you did.

106
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:29,610
Would you guys mind giving us a minute?

107
00:06:29,610 --> 00:06:32,190
Sure. Just keep an eye on the chick and duck.

108
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:34,300
Chick and the duck? Didn't they die--?

109
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:40,320
Dive. Yeah, they dove. Headfirst into fun on the farm.

110
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:49,080
So....

111
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:54,760
- Morning. - You too.

112
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:56,720
Last night was just wonderful.

113
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,800
Oh, it really was.

114
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:01,590
I woke up today with a big smile in my face.

115
00:07:01,590 --> 00:07:03,900
I know, me too. It was....

116
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:06,340
You know, it was one of those things

117
00:07:06,340 --> 00:07:07,870
you think is never going to happen.

118
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,360
And then it does,

119
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:11,990
and it's everything you want it to be.

120
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:14,840
I know. It was just....

121
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:19,080
It's just the perfect way to say goodbye.

122
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:29,090
Just a little bit more, honey.

123
00:07:29,090 --> 00:07:30,720
Oh, man, this hurts!

124
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,450
Is it really that bad?

125
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:33,890
I think it's time to kick you in the nuts

126
00:07:33,890 --> 00:07:36,030
and see which is worse.

127
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:40,520
The baby's head is crowning.

128
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,700
Oh, my God!

129
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,930
That is the most beautiful top of a head I have ever seen.

130
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:49,600
- Chandler, you have to see this. - I'm okay.

131
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,150
Chandler. You don't want to miss this.

132
00:07:52,150 --> 00:07:53,710
This is the birth of your child.

133
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:56,670
- It's the miracle of life. - All right.

134
00:07:58,980 --> 00:08:02,130
Wow, that is one disgusting miracle.

135
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:05,500
Start pushing. Here we go.

136
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:07,500
Here come the shoulders.

137
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:15,880
It's a boy.

138
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:19,400
- Is he okay? - He's just fine.

139
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:21,170
You did it.

140
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,190
It's a baby.

141
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:25,710
A beautiful little baby.

142
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:29,010
And some other stuff I'm gonna pretend I don't see.

143
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:34,320
- Would you like to cut the umbilical cord? - Okay.

144
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:39,850
Well, that's spongy.

145
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,180
Hey, handsome.

146
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:49,040
I'll love you so much that

147
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:52,090
no woman is ever gonna be good enough for you.

148
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,860
- We are so lucky. - I know.

149
00:08:58,410 --> 00:09:00,270
He has your eyes.

150
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:03,690
I mean, I know that's not possible,

151
00:09:03,690 --> 00:09:05,720
but he does.

152
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,130
We'll just get him cleaned up a bit.

153
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:13,080
Oh, my God, he's beautiful.

154
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,240
Thank you so much.

155
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,780
I'm really happy for you guys.

156
00:09:17,810 --> 00:09:20,960
- How do you feel? - I'm tired.

157
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:23,060
You don't have that much time to relax.

158
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:25,400
The other one will be along in a minute.

159
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:34,260
I'm sorry, who should be along in a what, now?

160
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,640
The next baby should be along in a minute.

161
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,910
We only ordered one.

162
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:45,710
- You know it's twins, right? - Oh, yeah.

163
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:48,710
These are the faces of two people in the know.

164
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:57,370
I can't believe you didn't know it's twins.

165
00:09:57,370 --> 00:09:58,680
This has never happened before.

166
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:02,270
Well, gosh. That makes me feel so special and good.

167
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,470
Wait. Did you know it was twins?

168
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:07,440
It's here in the paperwork we got from the clinic in Ohio.

169
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:10,560
- Did anybody tell you? - I don't think so.

170
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:13,590
They did mention two heartbeats,

171
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:15,780
but l thought it was just mine and the baby's.

172
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:17,630
They said, "Both heartbeats are strong."

173
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:20,480
And I thought, "Well, that's good, because I'm having a baby."

174
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,800
This is unbelievable.

175
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,550
Twins actually run in my family.

176
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:27,090
Interesting.

177
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:30,490
Can I see you for a second?

178
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:34,230
What do we do?

179
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:35,500
What do you mean, "What do we do?"

180
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,970
Twins!

181
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,090
Twins!

182
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,900
Chandler, you're panicking.

183
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,880
Join me, won't you?

184
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,190
What do you say we keep one

185
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:49,250
and then just have an option on the other one?

186
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:51,960
- We can't split them up. - Why not?

187
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,430
We could give each of them half a medallion.

188
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,500
And then years later, they'll find each other...

189
00:10:59,490 --> 00:11:01,520
...and be reunited.

190
00:11:01,610 --> 00:11:03,980
I mean, that's a great day for everybody.

191
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:07,320
What if the person who adopts the other one is horrible?

192
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,750
What if they're not?

193
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:10,510
What if it's adopted by a king?

194
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:13,780
Yeah. Because I hear the king is looking to adopt.

195
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:17,250
Monica, we are not ready to have two babies.

196
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:19,180
That doesn't matter.

197
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:21,100
We have waited so long for this.

198
00:11:21,110 --> 00:11:22,870
I don't care if it's two babies.

199
00:11:22,870 --> 00:11:24,400
I don't care if it's three babies.

200
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:28,650
I don't care if the entire cast of <i>Eight Is Enough</i> comes out of there.

201
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:31,080
We are taking them home

202
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,320
because they are our children.

203
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:34,970
Okay.

204
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,490
- Okay. - Okay!

205
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:39,900
Okay.

206
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:43,290
It looks like we're about ready over here.

207
00:11:43,290 --> 00:11:44,270
Come on, Erica.

208
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:45,900
Start pushing again now.

209
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:51,380
- Here she comes. - She? It's a girl?

210
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:52,720
Yeah.

211
00:11:54,660 --> 00:11:56,920
Well, now we have one of each.

212
00:11:58,010 --> 00:11:59,720
And that's enough.

213
00:12:03,410 --> 00:12:07,190
And then she said it was the perfect way to say goodbye.

214
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:10,550
Oh, my God. What did you say?

215
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:12,640
Nothing. What do you say to that?

216
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:15,260
You've got to tell her how you feel.

217
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:18,130
- No way. - Well, you can't just give up.

218
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:20,410
Is that what a dinosaur would do?

219
00:12:21,850 --> 00:12:22,460
What?

220
00:12:22,460 --> 00:12:25,200
Dude. I'm just trying to speak your language.

221
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:29,000
Ross, Rachel doesn't know that you even wanna get back together.

222
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,890
If she did, she might feel differently.

223
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:32,850
She might not even go.

224
00:12:33,780 --> 00:12:35,760
- You really think so? - I'm telling you!

225
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:38,450
Oh, ok, this is the part of the musical

226
00:12:38,450 --> 00:12:41,160
where there'd be a good, convincing song.

227
00:12:47,780 --> 00:12:48,550
Hi.

228
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,290
Can't a girl finish a song around here?

229
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:54,500
- Hey. - Hi. I dropped Emma off at my mom's.

230
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,610
- Okay. - You're not taking her tonight?

231
00:12:56,610 --> 00:13:01,370
No. We decided I'd set up, then my mom would bring Emma to Paris on Sunday.

232
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:03,360
Eight-hour flight with a one year old.

233
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,080
Good luck, Mom.

234
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:04,870
You kidding?

235
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:06,880
Eight hours with my mom talking about Atkins.

236
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,510
Good luck, Emma.

237
00:13:10,910 --> 00:13:12,210
All right. You know what? You're right.

238
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:14,420
I should at least tell her how I feel.

239
00:13:15,310 --> 00:13:17,420
- Ross. Wait, wait. - What? What?

240
00:13:17,420 --> 00:13:19,250
Could you get me a muffin?

241
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:25,180
- Rachel? - Yeah?

242
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,810
I know you're leaving tonight,

243
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:31,680
but I just have to tell you.

244
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:34,410
I love you.

245
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:40,240
Now, I don't know if that changes your plans at all.

246
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:44,840
But I thought you should know.

247
00:13:45,910 --> 00:13:47,590
Gunther.

248
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:51,720
I love you too.

249
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:54,580
Probably not in the same way.

250
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,310
But I do.

251
00:13:56,520 --> 00:14:00,060
And when I'm in a cafe having coffee...

252
00:14:00,060 --> 00:14:03,880
...or I see a man with hair brighter than the sun...

253
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,800
...I'll think of you.

254
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:15,690
- Bye, you guys. - Bye.

255
00:14:19,010 --> 00:14:20,760
Oh, my God!

256
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:24,000
Unbelievable.

257
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:25,270
Hey, you know what might help?

258
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:27,710
I'm not getting you a muffin!

259
00:14:37,970 --> 00:14:39,410
Do you think they recognize each other

260
00:14:39,410 --> 00:14:40,880
from in there?

261
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:44,430
Maybe. Unless they're like people who've lived in apartments...

262
00:14:44,430 --> 00:14:48,140
...next to each other for years, then one day they're pushed through a vagina...

263
00:14:48,140 --> 00:14:49,780
...and they meet.

264
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:53,520
We're going to take Erica to Recovery now.

265
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,980
There's something that we wanted to tell you.

266
00:14:57,080 --> 00:15:00,850
We decided to name the girl baby Erica.

267
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:04,740
Oh, my God, that's just like my name!

268
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,980
Son of a gun, it is.

269
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:13,090
Anyway, I'm gonna go get some rest.

270
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,590
I'm really glad I picked you guys.

271
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,420
You're gonna make great parents.

272
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,320
Even Chandler.

273
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:25,880
- Okay, well, bye. - Bye.

274
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,330
- We'll call you. - Okay.

275
00:15:27,330 --> 00:15:29,340
Have fun at church camp.

276
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:38,620
- Look at these little bunnies. - I know.

277
00:15:39,780 --> 00:15:41,500
You ready to trade?

278
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,710
- Okay. - Okay.

279
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:46,390
Okay. Let's see.

280
00:15:55,890 --> 00:15:58,290
- We could trade later. - Yeah, I'm good.

281
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,070
Hey, what are you working on?

282
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:06,180
A "welcome home" sign for the baby.

283
00:16:06,180 --> 00:16:09,560
How sweet! Oh, is that the baby?

284
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:12,090
No, I sat in the paint.

285
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,580
- Hey. - So did you talk to Rachel?

286
00:16:16,590 --> 00:16:19,690
- No. And I'm not going to. - What?

287
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:20,420
Why not?

288
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:22,260
She's just gonna shoot me down.

289
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:23,820
You guys saw what happened with Gunther.

290
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:25,140
That did not look like fun.

291
00:16:25,140 --> 00:16:28,030
How can you compare yourself to Gunther?

292
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:29,290
I mean, sure, he's sexy

293
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,440
in a more obvious way.

294
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:34,940
You have a relationship with her.

295
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:36,520
You slept together last night.

296
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,680
Yeah, and she still wants to go.

297
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,060
It's pretty clear where she is.

298
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:43,200
I know what you mean. I mean, sometimes--

299
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,580
- Joe. - Damn it!

300
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:47,950
If I were gonna tell her,

301
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:49,320
I don't have to do it now.

302
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,880
Okay? I'll be seeing her again. We've got time.

303
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,580
No, you don't. She's going to Paris!

304
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,260
She is going to meet somebody.

305
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:59,080
Do you know how many hot guys there are in Paris?

306
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:01,780
It's a city of Gunthers.

307
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,110
- Hey. - Hey.

308
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:07,660
What do you have there?

309
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:08,960
Oh, I made a little something.

310
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,860
If I had more time to work on it, it'd be better, but....

311
00:17:14,010 --> 00:17:16,070
Oh, my God, you did that yourself?

312
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:17,820
Honey, that's gorgeous.

313
00:17:17,820 --> 00:17:20,640
You know, the baby can't read, Mike.

314
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:25,030
Hi. You guys. The car service just got here.

315
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:26,750
I can't believe they're not home yet!

316
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,320
I have to catch my stupid plane.

317
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:29,570
I want to see the baby.

318
00:17:29,570 --> 00:17:31,260
Monica just called from the cab.

319
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:32,720
She said they should be here any minute.

320
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,360
Apparently, there's some big surprise.

321
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:37,240
Yeah, did she sound happy about it?

322
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,970
Because my friend Ethel's baby was born

323
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:41,330
with a teeny-tiny beard.

324
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:48,990
- Welcome home. - Oh, my God.

325
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:53,850
- Oh, my gosh. - Hey.

326
00:17:53,850 --> 00:17:55,360
Hey.

327
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:01,220
Hey, so, what is the big surprise?

328
00:18:05,290 --> 00:18:07,880
- Oh, my God! - How did this--?

329
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,180
Okay, awkward question.

330
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:11,820
The hospital knows you took two, right?

331
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:13,990
Yes. It's twins.

332
00:18:13,990 --> 00:18:15,420
Oh, my-- They are so cute.

333
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:18,090
Now, what kinds are they?

334
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:21,160
This is a boy. And that's a girl.

335
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,960
Her name is Erica.

336
00:18:23,710 --> 00:18:26,240
Hey, that pregnant girl's name was Erica.

337
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:30,690
Yeah. It's a shame you two didn't get to spend more time together.

338
00:18:31,910 --> 00:18:33,260
Yeah, and we named the boy Jack,

339
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:34,790
after Dad.

340
00:18:34,820 --> 00:18:36,780
He's gonna be so happy.

341
00:18:36,780 --> 00:18:38,840
Jack Bing. I love that.

342
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:41,230
It sounds like a '40s newspaper guy.

343
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:42,880
You know, "Jack Bing, <i>Morning Gazette.</i>

344
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,790
I'm gonna blow this story wide open."

345
00:18:50,010 --> 00:18:51,990
Oh, my gosh.

346
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:54,110
So beautiful.

347
00:18:54,110 --> 00:18:55,610
I want one.

348
00:18:55,610 --> 00:18:57,840
Oh, yeah? Well, tell me which one.

349
00:18:57,840 --> 00:19:00,090
I'll try to slip it in my coat.

350
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:02,930
Seriously.

351
00:19:02,930 --> 00:19:04,230
I mean, you want to make one of those?

352
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:06,300
One? How about a whole bunch?

353
00:19:06,300 --> 00:19:06,880
Really?

354
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,990
Yeah. We can teach them to sing,

355
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:11,690
and we could be like the von Trapp family.

356
00:19:12,190 --> 00:19:13,460
Only without the Nazis.

357
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:15,680
Although that sounds kind of dull.

358
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:18,390
I can't believe this.

359
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:19,060
If I don't leave now,

360
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:20,660
I'm gonna miss my plane.

361
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,460
I'm so glad you got to see the babies.

362
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:24,330
Me too.

363
00:19:24,450 --> 00:19:26,590
I'm just sorry I'm not gonna be around

364
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:29,520
to watch you two attempt to handle this.

365
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:34,820
All right. Oh, I can't say goodbye to you guys again.

366
00:19:34,930 --> 00:19:37,570
- I love you all so much. - Love you.

367
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,680
- We love you. - Call us when you get there.

368
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:43,580
I will. Ross, come here.

369
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:48,140
I just want you to know...

370
00:19:49,670 --> 00:19:51,430
...last night...

371
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:55,240
...I'll never forget it.

372
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,840
Neither will l.

373
00:20:06,350 --> 00:20:08,500
All right. Now I really have to go.

374
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:11,680
Okay, <i>au revoir</i>.

375
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:15,430
They're gonna really hate me over there.

376
00:20:18,090 --> 00:20:20,210
So you just let her go?

377
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,830
Yeah.

378
00:20:23,740 --> 00:20:26,910
- Hey, maybe that's for the best. - Yeah?

379
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:30,250
Yeah. You know, you just-- Look, you gotta--

380
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:33,100
You gotta think about last night the way she does.

381
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,270
Okay? You know, maybe....

382
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:39,970
Maybe sleeping together was the perfect way to say goodbye.

383
00:20:39,970 --> 00:20:42,210
Now she'll never know how he feels.

384
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:43,940
Maybe that's okay, you know?

385
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:46,830
Maybe it is better this way.

386
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:51,140
I mean, now.... Now you can move on.

387
00:20:51,330 --> 00:20:54,190
I mean, you've been trying to for so long.

388
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:56,970
Maybe now that you're on different continents....

389
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:58,800
Right?

390
00:21:03,150 --> 00:21:05,190
Maybe now you can actually do it, you know.

391
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:09,510
You can finally get over her.

392
00:21:13,930 --> 00:21:15,760
Yeah, that's true.

393
00:21:17,330 --> 00:21:18,770
Except....

394
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:23,180
I don't want to get over her.

395
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,070
What?

396
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:26,290
I don't. I want to be with her.

397
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:27,000
Really?

398
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,360
Yeah. I'm going to go after her.

399
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,070
Yeah, you are!

400
00:21:31,470 --> 00:21:34,560
Wait! Wait! Get your coat! Get your coat!

401
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,540
- My coat. - This is so cool!

402
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:38,070
I have no idea what's going on,

403
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:39,990
but I am excited!

404
00:21:39,990 --> 00:21:41,980
What do you think she's gonna say?

405
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:42,740
I don't know.

406
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:45,180
Even if she shoots me down,

407
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:47,330
at least I won't spend my life wondering...

408
00:21:47,330 --> 00:21:49,940
...what would have happened. Where is my coat?

409
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:51,980
You didn't bring one!

410
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,230
My cab's downstairs.

411
00:21:53,230 --> 00:21:54,500
I'll drive you to the airport.

412
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,050
- Wish me luck. - Hurry!

413
00:21:56,050 --> 00:21:57,370
Good luck!

414
00:22:08,490 --> 00:22:09,830
There's no seat belts!

415
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,680
That's okay. If we hit anything...

416
00:22:11,690 --> 00:22:12,980
...the engine will explode,

417
00:22:12,980 --> 00:22:16,080
so it's better if you're thrown from the car.

418
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:19,700
- All right, all right. Let's do this. - Okay!

419
00:22:21,570 --> 00:22:22,920
- Hey! - 80th and East End.

420
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,320
No. I don't take passengers.

421
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:26,490
The law makes you accept any fare.

422
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,810
You don't understand. This cab isn't real.

423
00:22:28,810 --> 00:22:30,860
What's your medallion number?

424
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:34,080
My medallion number is, get out of the cab!

425
00:22:34,090 --> 00:22:36,540
- What? - Get out of the cab!

426
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:46,090
Oh, hey, can I give you guys my housewarming gift now?

427
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:48,390
- Now, that you can do. - All right.

428
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:01,690
Chick Jr.? Duck Jr.?

429
00:23:03,670 --> 00:23:06,110
Don't hide from Mama!

430
00:23:14,910 --> 00:23:16,340
You can open your eyes now.

431
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:18,610
- Are we off the bridge? - Yes!

432
00:23:18,610 --> 00:23:21,190
Is the old woman on the bicycle still alive?

433
00:23:21,190 --> 00:23:23,910
Yeah, she jumped right back up.

434
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:27,060
Oh, my God. Phoebe, slow down!

435
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:28,850
Do you want to get to Rachel in time?

436
00:23:28,850 --> 00:23:31,120
Yes, but I don't want to die in your cab.

437
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:34,220
You should have thought of that before you got in!

438
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:37,010
- Tollbooth. - What?

439
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:38,810
Tollbooth!

440
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:42,910
Four bucks. There are quarters in the glove compartment.

441
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:45,130
Hurry!

442
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:46,620
Okay.

443
00:23:50,540 --> 00:23:52,830
Damn, that window's clean.

